            <div type="glosses" subtype="textual">
                <note xml:id="HANDGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">Unidentified fair&#x2010;copy hand (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSVII">MS VII</title>)&#x2014;</hi>For 
                    speculation concerning the hand responsible for this manuscript fair copy, see <ref type="note" subtype="bibliographical" target="hand_note.php#UNIDENTIFIEDMSSVII_XI">The Ruskin Family Handwriting: Unidentified Hands&#x2014;MS VII, XI Fair Copy of the <title type="composite" corresp="#JRACCOUNTTOUR">&#x201C;Account&#x201D;</title></ref>.</p></note>
                <!--The pointer to this gloss would be <ref type="gloss_textual" target="chamouni_poem_glosses_textual.php#HANDGLOSS" />.-->
                
                <note xml:id="STANZABREAKGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">&#x201C;For many ages pass unknown&#x2014; / Unknown save by a simple few&#x201D; 
                    (<title type="book" corresp="#JRPOEMS1891"><hi rend="italic">Poems</hi></title> [<date when="1891">1891</date>]; <title type="book" corresp="#JRWORKSLE"><hi rend="italic">Works</hi></title> [<date when="1903">1903</date>])&#x2014;</hi>Between 
                    these two lines, the editors of the <title type="book" corresp="#JRWORKSLE">Library Edition</title> insert an additional stanza break, not imposed by <persName corresp="#WGC">Collingwood</persName> 
                    in <title type="book" corresp="#JRPOEMS1891"><hi rend="italic">Poems</hi></title> (<date when="1891">1891</date>).</p></note>
                <!--The pointer to this gloss would be <ref type="gloss_textual" target="chamouni_poem_glosses_textual.php#STANZABREAKGLOSS" />.-->
                
                <note xml:id="DATELINEGLOSS" resp="#DCH"><p><hi rend="bold">Dateline (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSVII">MS VII</title>)&#x2014;</hi>For the datelines added at the bottom of the 
                    <title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSVII">MS VII</title> and <title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSXI">MS XI</title> transcriptions, and the dating and circumstances of transcribing these texts, 
                    see the apparatus, <ref type="apparatus" target="account_of_a_tour_on_the_continent_apparatus.php#COMPOSITEILLUSTRATEDTRAVELOGUEDRAFT">Account of a Tour on the Continent: Drafting the Composite&#x2010;Genre Travelogue (MS VII, MS VIII, MS XI)</ref>.</p></note>
